<br>
Make hotkey macros by going to your &quot;socials&quot; options, finding a blank button, right-click on it, and this brings up a box to write your hotkey.  Write in the name that will appear on the button &quot;e.g. assist&quot; at the top (and if you're using the new User Interface you can colour code them too).  In the lines below, type in the same commands that you would type in the chat window.  Example:<br>
<br>
/g I'm assisting %T to kill %P evil foe!<br>
/assist %T<br>
<br>
That one would say to your group (assuming you have groupmember Fred targetted):<br>
<br>
You tell your group, 'I'm assisting Fred to kill his evil foe!&quot;<br>
<br>
And then your target would switch to Fred's target (presumably the monster) and your autoattack would be turned on automatically (unless you previously turned 'attack on assist' off in your game options).<br>
<br>
If you go to Allakhazam and look in the &quot;emotes&quot; section you'll find a full explanation of what things like %T and %P and %O and %R do, and also various other emotes you can use.<br>
<br>
While looking around Allakhazams I'd also suggest you look under &quot;quests&quot; by zone, check Greater Faydark, and find out what you need for your quest armour, if you don't know already.  =)<br>
<br>
